          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstableview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " iterates every row in the table, accesses a cell via "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstableview/1534640-preparedcellatcolumn"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and requests the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscell/1532056-cellsize"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to find the appropriate largest width to use."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For accurate results and performance, it’s recommended that this method is implemented when using large tables. By default, large tables use a Monte Carlo simulation instead of iterating every row. "
            }
          ]
        }
